.Dd June 22, 2026
.Dt APPLE_FW 4
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm apple_fw
.Nd Apple EFI firmware properties driver
.Sh SYNOPSIS
To compile this driver into the kernel,
place the following line in your
kernel configuration file:
.Bd -ragged -offset indent
.Cd "device apple_fw"
.Ed
.Pp
Alternatively, to load the driver as a
module at boot time, place the following line in
.Xr loader.conf 5 :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
apple_fw_load="YES"
.Ed
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
driver extracts hardware configuration properties stored in the Apple
EFI firmware via the ACPI
.Fn _DSM
(Device Specific Method) interface.
.Pp
On Apple Macintosh computers, the EFI firmware populates ACPI device
nodes with a vendor-specific
.Fn _DSM
that returns key-value pairs describing hardware configuration such
as device model strings, firmware versions, and hardware addresses.
The
.Nm
driver identifies Apple ACPI root devices by the
.Ql AAPL
HID prefix, invokes
.Fn _DSM
with the Apple-specific UUID, and exposes the discovered properties
through the
.Xr sysctl 8
interface.
.Sh SYSCTL VARIABLES
Properties are exported under
.Va dev.apple_fw.0 :
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Va dev.apple_fw.0.<key>
Each property discovered from the EFI firmware is exposed as a
read-only sysctl node.
The key names and values are determined by the firmware and vary
by Mac model.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr acpi 4 ,
.Xr apple_smc 4 ,
.Xr sysctl 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
driver first appeared in
.Dx 6.5 .
